cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.IR 

The paper discusses the impact of extramural collaboration on research performance, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as the paper uses a bibliometric approach to measure collaboration through co-authorship of scientific publications. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) are also likely categories as the paper discusses policy measures aimed at fostering partnership and networking among the various components of the research system. cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are less likely categories, but still possible as the paper discusses the impact of collaboration on research productivity.
